      "message": "Current Dbus interface default value for SPDM communication is set to false \n\nname: Enabled\n    type: boolean\n    default: false\n    description: \u003e\n        Indicates whether SPDM communication is enabled.\n\nRequiring system administrators to use the Redfish API to enable SPDM communication or verify certificate on every SPDM-capable system is not a scalable approach.\n\nIMHO, the default value for SPDM communication should be set to true. \n\nAdditionally, there should be a mechanism to allow these default values to be configured or overridden at compile time. it is a generic requirement in any Daemon.",
